# Email Channels (EXAMPLE)

> Copy to `email_channels.md` and fill in real values. Canonical reference for your
> distinct sending identities and the email tooling available. **Read before
> sending or drafting any email** — never conflate accounts; verify the `From`
> address before declaring an email done.

## Identities

| Address | Purpose | Default for |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| <you@yourcompany.com> | General business | Default outbound |
| <outreach@yourcompany.com> | Cold outreach | Prospecting |
| <client-account@...> | A client-provided mailbox | That client only — never business mail |

## Tooling

- Describe how you send/draft mail (e.g. an account-explicit IMAP draft tool, a
  Workspace MCP with an explicit `user_email` param, etc.).
- **Gotcha to document for yourself:** if you use a connector that doesn't take an
  account parameter, confirm which mailbox it's bound to before trusting it.

## Rule

Verify the sender identity matches the purpose above before sending. When unsure
which identity applies, ask.
